Governor Abdullahi Ganduje of Kano State on Monday approved the appointment of Usman Muhammad as the new Head of Service. Until his appointment, Muhammad was the Permanent Secretary at the Ministry of Information. Also appointed as Permanent Secretary was Muhammad Shehu, who until his elevation, was the Director, Research and Statistics, Kano Roads Maintenance Agency. Magaji Lawan was also promoted to Permanent Secretary and he is now Director, Accounts, Ministry of Finance; Bilyaminu Gambo Zubairu, who was also Director PHC, Rano Zonal Office, is now a Permanent Secretary. In a statement, the Chief Press Secretary to the Governor, Abba Anwar, said Mairo Dambatta, Director in the Office of the Head of Service, is now a Permanent Secretary. The appointments are with immediate effect. While congratulating them on their newly assigned responsibilities, Ganduje enjoined them to always work hard for the promotion of good virtues in public service.  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com